summary: This is a search and seizure warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York, authorizing the search of compact discs (FBI evidence numbers 15, 16, 17, 18, 22) seized from 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, on or about July 7, 2019. The warrant seeks evidence related to violations of 18 U.S.C. §§ 371 and 1591 (sex trafficking conspiracy and sex trafficking of minors).

keyFacts: The warrant authorizes the search of compact discs (FBI evidence numbers 15, 16, 17, 18, 22) seized from 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, on or about July 7, 2019.
The search is for evidence of violations of Title 18, U.S.C., Sections 371 (conspiracy) and 1591 (sex trafficking of minors).
Items to be seized include communications regarding victims, photographs of teenage girls or younger, child erotica, and records of device ownership/use.
The warrant allows law enforcement to create forensic images of the devices and use various techniques (keyword searches, file review, metadata analysis) to locate responsive data.
The warrant was issued by U.S. Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses and was to be executed on or before July 21, 2019.
